	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-06-03T23:01:35">Vesuvius plc is engaged in the molten metal flow engineering business. The Company provides its products and services principally to the steel and foundry industries. The Company operates through two segments: Steel and Foundry. The Steel division provides flow control and advanced refractories solutions for the global steel industry. The Company's Foundry division supplies consumable products, solutions and associated services to the foundry industry and trades under the Foseco brand. The Steel division consists of two product lines, Steel Flow Control and Advanced Refractories. The Advanced Refractories product line includes refractory materials for lining steelmaking vessels, such as blast furnaces, ladles and tundishes. The Company has operations in around 38 countries across the world, including around 16 production sites in the Americas, approximately 29 production sites in Europe, the Middle East and Africa (EMEA), and around 20 production sites in Asia-Pacific.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-02-17T08:50:11">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, Vesuvius PLC revenues decreased 4% to L702.6M. Net income decreased 8% to L35.2M. Revenues reflect Foundry segment decrease of 6% to L226.3M, Steel segment decrease of 3% to L476.3M. Net income also reflects Steel segment income decrease of 6% to L44.5M, Exceptional Items segment loss increase of 33% to L10.5M. Dividend per share remained flat at L0.05.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
